Project Setup and Execution Guide

Executing all notebook cells sequentially is a critical requirement to ensure the correct functioning 
of the project. Each cell is designed to perform a specific task, including data loading, 
preprocessing, model initialization, and application setup. Skipping or running cells out of order 
may lead to missing dependencies, undefined variables, or incomplete configurations, which can 
cause errors or unexpected behavior. 
Therefore, it is essential to run all cells from start to finish to guarantee that the system operates 
smoothly and that the web application is deployed as intended. 

Step 1: Upload Project Files to Google Drive 
First, upload the project folder to Google Drive with the name: 

MARBERT_Sentiment_Project 
The folder must include the following: 
• Dataset file: CompanyReviews.csv  
• Pre-trained model folder: sentiment_model  
• UI image required for the interface  

Importance of this step: 
This step ensures that all project components are stored in a centralized and accessible 
location. It allows seamless integration with the Colab environment for loading data and 
model files. 

Step 2: Upload the Notebook to Google Colab 
Upload the Jupyter Notebook file to Google Colab. 
Importance of this step: 
Google Colab provides a cloud-based execution environment with optional GPU support, 
which enhances performance when handling NLP models and large datasets.

Step 3: Execute Notebook Cells Sequentially 
Run the notebook cells one by one in sequence. 
Importance of this step: 
Sequential execution ensures that all preprocessing, configurations, and dependencies are 
properly initialized before moving to the next steps, preventing runtime errors. 

Step 4: Mount Google Drive and Load Dataset 
Before accessing the dataset, mount Google Drive using: 
from google.colab import drive 
drive.mount('/content/drive') 
Then load the dataset: 
import pandas as pd 
file_path = 
"/content/drive/MyDrive/MARBERT_Sentiment_Project/CompanyReviews.csv" 

df = pd.read_csv(file_path) 

Importance of this step: 
Mounting Google Drive establishes a connection between Colab and your stored files, 
enabling direct access to the dataset required for processing and model input.

Step 5: Continue Execution Until Model Stage 
Proceed with running the remaining cells until reaching the model stage. 

Step 6: Model Usage Options 
At this stage, users have two options: 
Option A: Train the Model 
Uncomment and run the training code provided in the notebook. 
Option B (Recommended for faster execution and demonstration purposes):  
Load Pre-trained Model 
Load the pre-trained model from Google Drive: 
from transformers import AutoTokenizer, 
AutoModelForSequenceClassification 
model_path = 
"/content/drive/MyDrive/MARBERT_Sentiment_Project/sentiment_model" 
tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_path) 
model = 
AutoModelForSequenceClassification.from_pretrained(model_path) 
 
 
Uncomment and run the training code provided in the notebook. (Not preferable) 
