Importance of this step: 
Using a pre-trained model significantly reduces computational time and resources while 
maintaining high performance. 
 
Step 7: Install Required Libraries 
Install Streamlit: 
!python3 -m pip install -q streamlit 
 
Install translation library: 
!pip -q install deep-translator 
 
 
 
Install Cloudflare tunnel: 
!wget -q 
https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared/releases/latest/downloa
d/cloudflared-linux-amd64.deb 
!dpkg -i cloudflared-linux-amd64.deb 
Importance of this step: 
These libraries are required to build and deploy the web-based user interface and enable 
additional features such as translation and public access. 

Step 8: Launch the Web Application 
After running all cells, execute the final cell: 
!grep -a -o 'https://.*trycloudflare.com' tunnel.log 
A link will appear. Click it to access the deployed web application. 
Importance of this step: 
This step exposes the local Streamlit app to the internet via a secure tunnel, allowing users 
to interact with the system through a web interface. 

Note: 
The steps outlined above are provided for clarification purposes. 
However, all procedures and implementations are already fully 
defined within the notebook code. Therefore, it is essential to 
execute all cells sequentially to ensure the web application functions 
correctly and as intended. 
